<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="78" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Brazil. S. Salvador, 5 Apr 1944, Rick 20847 (holotype PACA, by original designation).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="78">
For a description, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hjortstam, K" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" pagination="261 - 276" title="Studies in tropical Corticiaceae (Basidiomycetes) IV. Type studies of taxa described by J. Rick." volume="15" year="1982">Hjortstam and Ryvarden (1982)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorjon, SP" journalOrPublisher="Mycosphere" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" pagination="464 - 474" title="Some species of Hyphodontia s. l. with encrusted cystidial elements." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/3/4/10" volume="3" year="2012">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gorjón">Gorjon</normalizedToken>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
could not verify the presence of large capitate cystidia, similar to those present in 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. magnifica" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" rank="species" species="magnifica">X. magnifica</taxonomicName>
and included in the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hjortstam, K" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" pagination="261 - 276" title="Studies in tropical Corticiaceae (Basidiomycetes) IV. Type studies of taxa described by J. Rick." volume="15" year="1982">Hjortstam and Ryvarden (1982)</bibRefCitation>
. We restudied the isotype in herbarium O and can confirm that these large cystidia do exist, which supports a possible position of this species close to 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. detriticus" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" rank="species" species="detriticus">X. detriticus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. pruinosus" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" rank="species" species="pruinosus">X. pruinosus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
